@759 = ~Infernal Shout~
@7510 = ~Infernal Shout (Alteration)
Level: 5
Range: 0
Duration: special
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 9-meters radius
Saving Throw: special

This spell amplifies to extreme the yell uttered by the warlord at the end of casting to turn it into a devastating sound wave. All creatures who hear the cry, with the exception of the caster and party members who recognize the casting spell quick enough to cover their ears (saving throw vs. breath) will suffer different effects depending upon the level of the caster, according to the following table:
Level 9: 10D4 damage, deafness for 1D4 +2 rounds if the saving throw is successful
Level 12: 12D4 damage, deafness for 1 turn, 1D4 +2 rounds only if the saving throw is successful
Level 16: 14D4 damage, deafness for 1 turn, stun for 1D6 rounds if the saving throw is failed
Level 20: 16D4 damage, deafness for 12 rounds, stun for 1D4 +2 rounds, 1D2 rounds only if the saving throw is successful
Any damage inflicted by this spell can be halved by a successful saving throw vs. spells. The same saving throw determines the secondary side effects.
Damage inflicted by this spell can not kill a creature. That whose total hp points is less than damage received will have 1 hp and faints.
A creature deafened by this spell can no longer be affected and can not be affected by other wails (Banshee, Lich, etc.) before having recovered normal hearing.~
