The warlord must to be in contact with the soil when he casts this spell, otherwise it will have no effect. When the spell is cast, an outer skin of stone comes to cover the mage and becoming a second skin. This magical skin does not bother him and immunizes him against hits. The enemies of the mage can destroy the stoneskin by hitting it a number of times equal to half the level of the mage plus one. As an example, the warlord of level 14 protected by stoneskin could withstand without damage 8 hits before that protection is shattered.
