@7517 = ~Draconic Strength~
@7518 = ~Draconic Strength (Alteration, Enchantment)
Level: 5
Range: 0
Duration: 5 rounds + 1 round/2 levels
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

It's by looking to give himself the strength of a dragon that the warlord found this strange spell. The latter performs an incomplete polymorph to the mage: it does not modify at all his appearance, but charges his body by a powerful magic energy that grants him all the attributes of a dragon. His armor class, his Hit Dice (+4 extra HP by dice of overnumbered life than those of a mage) and his magic resistance vary, and he gets immunity to an element as well as the half of the combat modifier (in addition to all melee damage) of this dragon.
In fact, the granted power while casting the spell is random at the option of two dice rolls, which vary according to the level of the mage:
Level 9 to 13 : 1D4
Level 14 to 18: 1D6
Level 19+     : 1D8

The first result determines the type of dragon:
1: White Dragon
2: Black Dragon
3: Copper Dragon
4: Blue Dragon
5: Bronze Dragon
6: Silver Dragon
7: Red Dragon
8: Golden Dragon

and the second determines the age of the dragon:
1: Juvenile
2: Young Adult
3: Adult
4: Middle Age
5: Old
6: Very Old
7: Venerable
8: Worm

The transformed wizard does not create an aura of terror and does not get the breath of dragon, or any other special dragon skill.
He can not be under several draconic strengths.~
